translated:
Ehrenkrona, Signe Emmy Andrea, Baroness, Hulterstad, Mjölby, born on October 27, 1877 in Jönköping, to consul Anders Gustaf Westman and Emmy Maria Sofia Westring. Married in 1899 to Lieutenant, Baron Carl-Erik E. Children: Anna born in 1903, married to Foreign Councilor and law graduate Gösta Engzelil, Erik born in 1904, Major, Märta born in 1905, married to Docent at Stockholm University and archivist Olof Jägerskiöld, Carl-Gustaf born in 1909, employed at the clearinghouse in Stockholm, Henrik born in 1914, Phil. Mag., married to Veronica Martin. Attended Västra elem:lärov. and further courses at Ahlinska sk. in Stockholm. Former chairman of the Mjölby Right Women's Association, chairman of the Mjö'l'by-Vi-foilka local association of the Östergötland Children's Society, vice chairman of the Mjölby branch of the Red Cross, former chairman of the Mjölby Girls' Scout group, and member of the church council in Mjölby. Awarded the Royal Order of King Mårten and the Illis quorum meruere Labores Medal.

Ehrenström-Borgström, Elsa Josefina, Dentist, Fårösund, born on April 3, 1905 in Rone, Gotland County, daughter of former vicar L. A. Ehrenström and Emma Nilsson. Married from 1940 to 1944 to dentist Earl Borgström. Completed her high school studies at Linköping private gymnasium, among others in 1927. Studied dentistry at the universities of Rostock, Kiel, Freiburg, and Munich, earned a German dentistry degree at Rostock in 1933, and a Swedish dentistry degree in 1937. Had her practice in Fårösund since 1937 and worked as an assistant dentist at the Eastman Institute in Stockholm from 1938-1939.
